		("LOC_LOADING_INFO_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG",  
		"Step forth King Bayinnaung! Bend the nations around you into submission! Through diplomacy and stength of arms you will force the kings of the world into loyalty, and the tribute they pay you will spur your soldiers ever onwards. With their allegiance and obligation you will spread Burma's glory across the globe!"  	),
		("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"That's rather disappointing."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"I am honored."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"You show great potential. Let us work together in friendship!"),
		("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"No, first you must prove yourself."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"I am honored."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DECLARE_WAR_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"I have thought long and hard. It is time you join the ranks of my many vassals."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DECLARE_WAR_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"Another betrayal? This is proof I am too trusting"),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DEFEAT_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"My vassals seem to have failed me. I congratulate you on your victory."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DEFEAT_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"My vassals seem to have failed me. I congratulate you on your victory."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DELEGATION_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"I send an image of the lord Buddha for your people, and a longyi for yourself."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DELEGATION_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"I cannot accept."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DELEGATION_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"Thank you. Tribute for Burma is always welcome."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DENOUNCE_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"I really should come in and depose you. You are not fit to rule. (Denounces You)"),
		("LOC_DIPLO_DENOUNCE_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"Another betrayal. This is proof I am too trusting."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"You have the honour of meeting the King of Burma, Bayinnaung Kyawhtin Nawratha. Prove to me your strength, and perhaps we can be allies."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_VISIT_RECIPIENT_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"I have a city nearby, although come to think of it I'm unsure if it's mine or my vassal's city."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_NEAR_INITIATOR_POSITIVE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"Wonderful."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_NO_MANS_INFO_EXCHANGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"Workmen are just putting the finishing touches on my palace. I invite you to see its splendour."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_GREETING_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"Hail."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_WARNING_EXIT_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"Be warned. Your puny nation stands in the way of Burma's glory."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_KUDO_EXIT_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"I have been watching your conquests with great interest. They are impressive indeed."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_ALLIANCE_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"Ally with me! Your strength is admirable!"),
		("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_MAKE_DEAL_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"{LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY}"),
		("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_MAKE_DEAL_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"{LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY}"),
		("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_PEACE_AI_ACCEPT_DEAL_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"Well fought. We have both earned this peace."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_PEACE_AI_REFUSE_DEAL_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"No. I cannot accept."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_PEACE_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"Enough, you have proven your mettle. Let us end this."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_OPEN_BORDERS_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"You may, but do not linger."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_OPEN_BORDERS_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"What general would permit such a liability?"),
		("LOC_DIPLO_OPEN_BORDERS_FROM_AI_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                     
		"I demand passage through your lands. It is a matter of vital importance."),
		("LOC_DIPLO_WARNING_TOO_MANY_TROOPS_NEAR_ME_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_ANY",                                      
		"If you are trying to intimidate us with your army, it’s not working. Move them, or face the consequences."),
--------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Quote and Pedia
--------------------------------------------------------------------
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_QUOTE",  
		"As long as they have the four white elephants, Burma and Ayutthaya will be like water and earth."  	),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_TITLE",
		"Bayinnaung"),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_SUBTITLE",
		"King of Burma"),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_CAPSULE_BODY",
		"The Burmese empire is one where culture and faith work to support a army without parallel. Bayinnaung bends city-states to his will to enhance Burma's military might."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_DETAILED_BODY",
		"Burma is an initially very flexible civ, building Holy Sites, Theater Squares, or Encampments will provide a small boost to [ICON_Faith] Faith and [ICON_Culture] Culture that scales to your current output, helping you from lagging behind when you use the second part of their unique ability to quickly build up an army. Payas further boost your culture and military might, providing [ICON_Culture] Culture and increasing your army's strength. Under Bayinnaung, city-states will quickly prove valuable vassals, providing a Heavy Cavalry unit as a levy and providing [ICON_Gold] as tribute in addition to the usual bonuses they provide."),		
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1",
		"Considered one of the three greatest kings of Burma, along with Anawrahta and Alaungpaya, Bayinnaung Kyawhtin Nawrahta was king of Toungoo Dynasty of Burma from 1550 to 1581. During his 31-year reign, which has been called the “greatest explosion of human energy ever seen in Burma”, Bayinnaung assembled the largest empire in the history of Southeast Asia, which included much of modern-day Burma, Chinese Shan states, Lan Na, Lan Xang, Manipur and Siam."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_2",
		"On 30 April 1550, Bayinnaung’s predecessor and brother-in-law Tabinshwehti was assassinated by his own bodyguards on the order of Smim Htaw, one of the king’s close advisers. Smim Htaw naturally proclaimed himself king. But so did all other major governors and viceroys—including Bayinnaung’s own brother Minkhaung II. Although Bayinnaung had been Tabinshwehti’s chosen heir apparent since 1542, none of them acknowledged Bayinnaung as the rightful successor. The Toungoo Empire, which Bayinnaung had helped forge for the last 16 years, lay in ruins. Bayinnaung, as a colonial era historian noted, was “a king without a kingdom”."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_3",
		"Bayinnaung marched south, captured the city of Pegu, and executed the rebel leader, Smim Htaw. The other Mon rulers then surrendered, and the revolt was at an end. Bayinnaung made Pegu his capital, as Tabinshwehti had. Bayinnaung then set out against Shan chiefs, who occupied the ancient Burmese capital of Ava. He captured it the following year. The Shans were placed under Burmese suzerainty, and Bayinnaung was consequently in a position to attack his most powerful enemy, Siam."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_4",
		"In 1563 Bayinnaung took as a pretext for war the refusal of the Siamese to acknowledge his suzerainty. The following year he captured the Siamese capital of Ayutthaya and brought the Siamese royal family to Burma as hostages. In 1568, when a revolt flared up, Bayinnaung again invaded Siam. Because the Siamese put up fierce resistance, Ayutthaya was not captured until August 1569. Bayinnaung installed a new vassal on the throne and deported thousands of Siamese into Burma as slaves. The Burmese would dominate Siam for more than 15 years."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_5",
		"The year was 1576 and the states Bayinnaung had conquered had all quieted down and stabilised. Many rival kingdoms in the area were eager to have his support. Bayinnaung saw himself as the protector of Theravada Buddhism and had assembled the largest empire in Indochinese history spanning from Manipur to Cambodian and Yunnan. It was entirely possible that he had also been continuously receiving homage from Vietnam and Cambodia. Bayinnaung started his reign as a king without a kingdom, and ruled as an emperor without an empire. He did not annex lands, but simply conquered their kings. The empire was held together not by any formal institution of power, but by personal relationships with the vassal kings and queens. He presented himself as the Sekyawaddy, the Universal Ruler and ruled the empire on the basis of Thitsa and Kyaezu: Allegiance and Obligation. Bayinnaung personally only ever ruled Pegu directly."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_6",
		"This decentralised system meant that Bayinnaung only introduced reforms at the margins and let the local rulers rule as they had before. From the sheer size of the empire, this was the only way Bayinnaung could retain power. Perhaps the most important reform that Bayinnaung introduced was that of administering the Shan Saophas. He regularly removed the Saopha (king) for gross misconducts and chose a successor from the Saopha’s family. He also required that the sons of all his vassal rulers be taught and trained in Pegu. This served both to create a hostage situation should a rebellion occur, but also to introduce Burmese court culture to their vassal states in the future. Although the empire would quickly fall apart after his death, the system continued with the Shan states so much so that it brought an end to the constant Shan raids that had plagued prior kings."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_7",
		"Bayinnaung also standardised the legal code in much of his empire by prescribing an official collection of law books: the Dhammathat Kyaw and Kothaungchok. The new legal system was adopted and modified to be compatible with local practices, but was ultimately a large standardisation in law. Bayinnaung also promoted a standardised set of measurements: using the Burmese customary units across the empire. To this day, Burma still uses many of Bayinnaung’s units. The Burmese Calendar was also adopted in Siam and some regions of other parts of Southeast Asia until the 19th century."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_8",
		"Another enduring legacy of Bayinnaung was his introduction of a more orthodox Theravada Buddhism to Upper Burma and the Shan states. He propagated the religious reforms begun by King Dhammazedi in the late 1470s. Viewing himself as the “model Buddhist king,” the king distributed copies of the scriptures, fed monks, and built pagodas at every new conquered state from Upper Burma and Shan states to Lan Na and Siam. He prohibited all human and animal sacrifices throughout the kingdom. In particular, he forbade the Shan practice of killing the slaves and animals belonging to a saopha at his funeral. His attempts to rid of animist nat worship from Buddhism, however, failed."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_9",
		"By 1580, not only had the Bayinnaung subdued all the countries which had occupied his attention for the last three decades but he also had the respect from neighboring states. He faced no internal or external threats. Instead of resting, he turned his gaze on Arakan, the kingdom he and Tabinshwehti unsuccessfully tried to conquer in 1545–1547. He determined that it was now time to reduce the western coastal kingdom to the vassal status it held under the Pagan kings once more. The king sent an 8000-strong naval invasion force on 15 October 1580. The naval fleet, which consisted of 200 ships, went on to occupy Sandoway in November 1580. The king had probably planned to lead the assault on the Arakanese capital Mrauk-U by himself but could not because of his failing health. The invasion force remained inactive at Sandoway for a year. The king sent additional land and naval forces (29,000 troops, 1600 horses, 120 elephants) on 28 August 1581 in preparation for the coming dry season campaign. But the king died six weeks later, and the invasion forces withdrew soon after."),
		("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_SUK_BAYINNAUNG_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_10",
		"His eldest son and heir-apparent Nanda took over the throne without incident. But the empire, which Bayinnaung had built on military conquests and maintained by both military power and personal relationships with the vassal rulers, was to crumble soon after. The first crack appeared in the far north in September 1582 when Chinese Shan states of Sanda and Thaungthut revolted. The rebellion was put down in March 1583. Much more serious cracks followed. Ava (Upper Burma) revolted in October 1583, and the rebellion was put down on 24 April 1584. Siam revolted on 3 May 1584. Nanda would spend the rest of his reign fighting Siam and other former vassals and would lose the entire empire in the process by 1599.");			
